# Technical_Design

## 1. Applies when
Strong technical constraints — engine limits, network sync, AI, procedural
generation, or tooling.

## 2. This document owns
Technical constraints; implementation assumptions; engine limits; data structures;
sync requirements; performance budgets; tooling needs.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Design intent (that is the design docs); gameplay numbers; narrative.

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Document role · 2. Constraints · 3. Implementation assumptions ·
4. Data structures · 5. Sync requirements · 6. Performance budgets · 7. Tooling · 8. TODO

## 5. Common boundaries
- Technical vs Gameplay — implementation limits vs design numbers.
- Technical vs Multiplayer — netcode/sync vs multiplayer rules.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Technical constraints reference design docs, do not redefine design intent.
- Performance budgets are single-owned here.
